  <prompt>
    Convert the PB-009 section of the task-120 audit document into a concrete remediation plan. Per Q17 owner directive: PB-009 is the canonical specialized NDA playbook after WP6 enrichment — do NOT delete. Plan must specify: (1) the rewritten description text (embedding-friendly), (2) the JPS `$ref` composition (Skills + Knowledge), (3) the `sprk_jpsmatchingmetadata` JSON payload, (4) the target `sprk_playbookcode` value (`summarize-nda`), (5) any node-graph adjustments needed for Path 3 compatibility. Output: `notes/handoffs/121-pb009-remediation-plan.md`. This plan is the input for task 130.
  </prompt>

  <role>SPAARKE platform developer + AI playbook author. Translates audit findings into actionable remediation specs.</role>

  <goal>
    A concrete, executable remediation plan for PB-009 captured at `notes/handoffs/121-pb009-remediation-plan.md`. Plan specifies EVERY field change task 130 will apply, the JPS `$ref` composition text, the `sprk_jpsmatchingmetadata` JSON, and the embedding-friendly description rewrite. The plan is reviewed by the owner before task 130 commits.
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      Per spec FR-43 + design §WP6 Reconciliation §3 (Recommendation: keep PB-009, review, update to current standard). Q17 owner directive forbids deletion. PB-009 becomes the canonical specialized NDA playbook after WP6 — it's the cleanest path because it already exists in Dataverse as a system playbook. Task 130 applies the plan; this task authors it.
    </background>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>projects/spaarke-ai-platform-chat-routing-redesign-r1/notes/handoffs/120-pb-audit.md</file>
